Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.17,0:12:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Apple Pay sheet is intended
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a summary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.71,0:12:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, use these line items to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.27,0:12:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,explain additional charges,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,discounts, tax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.14,0:12:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to the Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.07,0:12:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,store and show you what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.09,0:12:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you'll see I'm buying an
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.49,0:13:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad and here in the sheet I see
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.79,0:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a subtotal, shipping, tax, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,total.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, very top level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes you don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.16,0:13:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're going to charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.96,0:13:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you're a ride sharing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,company and you don't actually
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.04,0:13:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,charge the user until the ride
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.64,0:13:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.03,0:13:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you want to add an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.89,0:13:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,optional gratuity that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.49,0:13:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,picks at the end of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.14,0:13:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,transaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use pending items to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.95,0:13:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,disclose that these pending
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.21,0:13:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,items are additional costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.14,0:13:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example, we just mark
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.24,0:13:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the type as pending, and it will
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,show up on the Apple Pay sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.95,0:13:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,without an amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the total amount has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nonnegative.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really make sense to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.69,0:13:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,have a payment that's for a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.58,0:13:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,negative amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.10,0:13:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can be pending.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can have a total that is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,not known at the time the time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:13:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the transaction is taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.24,0:14:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very important for the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,total amount to use the business
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,name that will appear on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.23,0:14:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,card statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important for two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Firstly, users want to be able
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to reconcile what appears within
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.73,0:14:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Wallet application and on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.11,0:14:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,their bank statement with what
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.57,0:14:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, now that we support the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,new Mac Book Pro with Touch Bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.88,0:14:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we actually show the merchant's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.53,0:14:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,name on the Touch Bar itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.81,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again, it's important to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that it matches what
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.39,0:14:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the user expects.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.68,0:14:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one use case that's grown
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,over the last year with Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay is subscriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.98,0:14:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, news sites that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.18,0:14:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,want to use Apple Pay on the web
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.82,0:14:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to take subscriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.57,0:14:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that, but there's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.98,0:14:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,some advice I'd like to give
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.29,0:14:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to clarify the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.72,0:14:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,subscription details prior to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to include line
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.12,0:14:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,items that reiterate the billing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.88,0:14:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.46,0:14:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And for variable subscriptions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.64,0:14:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,use pending items.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:14:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give you an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.75,0:14:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a little side job, a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.28,0:15:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,little app I'm working, it sells
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.74,0:15:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,avocado toast to na√Øve
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,millennials.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.37,0:15:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a subscription, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's what's getting
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,all the funding, so I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's my Apple Pay sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.77,0:15:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that I have here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.27,0:15:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,weekly service, so in my line
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.02,0:15:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,item I'm clearly indicating the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.31,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,length of time that the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,subscription is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also noting a discount.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.55,0:15:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that in the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.56,0:15:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can note introductory
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,discounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what will be charged at
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this current time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.29,0:15:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can use the same
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,information, the same payment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.97,0:15:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,data you get from Apple Pay to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,make subsequent charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.57,0:15:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes there are certain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.42,0:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,types of subscriptions where the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,cost varies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.56,0:15:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're a meal ordering
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.16,0:15:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,service and the number of meals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.02,0:15:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user gets varies week
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by week, month by month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Use pending amounts for variable
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.78,0:15:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,subscriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing to bear in mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.54,0:15:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that if your subscription is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,variable, and the user changes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:15:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,their plan, for example, you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:15:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,only need to show the payment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sheet if a change is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,result in additional fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.62,0:16:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user decreases the cost
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.64,0:16:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the payment sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.55,0:16:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk now about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.98,0:16:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically, I want to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,about the Apple Pay buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.98,0:16:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, use the built-in Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.98,0:16:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't create your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple reasons why you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.77,0:16:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.48,0:16:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Firstly, the Apple Pay buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are localized to any language
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user can choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.25,0:16:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're also vectors, so they're
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.83,0:16:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,completely scalable, so you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,don't need to worry about them
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not looking right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.69,0:16:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're available in a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.07,0:16:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,number of styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.53,0:16:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We first introduced the native
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.22,0:16:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons in iOS 8.3.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can target 8.3 and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.25,0:16:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,above, which is nearly the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.14,0:16:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,entire in store base right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.18,0:16:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And in macOS 10.12.1 and iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.07,0:16:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,10.1 we made it a little easier
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.25,0:16:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on web.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.98,0:17:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We used simplified CSS styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give you some examples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.75,0:17:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,some code examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here is the not very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.06,0:17:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting code in Swift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.89,0:17:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentButton is a UI button
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.74,0:17:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.47,0:17:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You just provide a type and a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,style.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.46,0:17:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We have buttons in black, white,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and white with an outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.63,0:17:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you the same button
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.61,0:17:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the new CSS style it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.83,0:17:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was introduced in iOS 10.1.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a WebKit appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,style Apple Pay button, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.76,0:17:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,type buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have four button styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.12,0:17:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.82,0:17:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,On the left are the Swift
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.69,0:17:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,symbols, on the right the CSS
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.79,0:17:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,names.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a plain button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.86,0:17:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a buy with Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.36,0:17:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have a Set up Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.78,0:17:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see how to use that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.55,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And new in iOS 10.2 and macOS
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,10.12.3, we have a Donate with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.74,0:18:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay button if you're a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.61,0:18:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,nonprofit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.61,0:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, obviously as a nonprofit,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably want to target all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,versions of iOS or macOS before
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, you can just fall
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the regular plain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the quick update on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.02,0:18:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay over the past year and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.56,0:18:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a review of some of our best
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.35,0:18:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to tell you the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting part of the talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.17,0:18:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is what's new with Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.30,0:18:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When we thought about what we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.73,0:18:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,could do this year with Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay we thought how could we make
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.24,0:18:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a best in class conversion even
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.71,0:18:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And how could we help users
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.96,0:18:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,resolve common problems that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they told us about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.58,0:18:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, how can we help
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,make getting started with Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.21,0:18:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay fast and easy, so even more
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of your potential customers can
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,come with cards already on their
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.01,0:18:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I think you'll see that the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.93,0:18:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,next few slides will show some
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.04,0:18:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ways we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.75,0:18:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.68,0:18:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The first way is through Set up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.59,0:18:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.33,0:19:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, starting with this version
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.64,0:19:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of iOS, we strongly recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.05,0:19:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that you show the Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.09,0:19:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,button for all devices that are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.85,0:19:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,hardware capable with Apple Pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can choose the Set up or
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.11,0:19:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy button stars that suit your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.66,0:19:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.10,0:19:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If the API tells you the user
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.12,0:19:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have any cards, you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.73,0:19:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,could optionally display Set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If it makes more sense in your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.29,0:19:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,design to stick with Buy, you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.94,0:19:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.92,0:19:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've introduced something
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to really help with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for this new
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,advice is because now we support
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.82,0:19:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,inline set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.75,0:19:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay Set up is now offered
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.57,0:19:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.88,0:19:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to present an Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.31,0:19:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay sheet on previous versions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of iOS, if the user didn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,any cards, that would actually
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.54,0:19:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you wouldn't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.23,0:19:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to present the view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you will actually present,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.53,0:19:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or present Apple Pay Set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.22,0:19:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And most importantly, users are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.99,0:19:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,returned to the purchase as soon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as set up completes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:19:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that it's actually
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.73,0:19:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,faster than a manual check out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.61,0:19:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to add and Apple Pay card and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.99,0:19:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,complete the purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to actually show you what
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.15,0:20:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that looks like and how quick it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here is the Apple store, on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.98,0:20:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,their website this time, not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,their app.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to see what
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,happens when we try to tap the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy button without cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.71,0:20:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to go quite quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.58,0:20:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we get a little
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.42,0:20:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,dialogue to add a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.10,0:20:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to add a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.92,0:20:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a card that I've already
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.23,0:20:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,used on another phone, so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.48,0:20:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.89,0:20:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just enter my security code.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to add the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.52,0:20:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the terms thoroughly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.80,0:20:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.31,0:20:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to add it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.50,0:20:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to Wallet, activate the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.43,0:20:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And boom, we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.86,0:20:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.83,0:20:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately we're going to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.86,0:20:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apple Pay sheet so we can
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,continue the payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That actually took less than 30
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.34,0:20:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds, which is still much
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.79,0:20:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,faster than manually typing my
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.07,0:20:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,card number and all this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,information on the regular Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:20:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Store checkout.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, this happens
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.33,0:21:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,completely automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to make any code
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.85,0:21:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no new API.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.53,0:21:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is present
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay if the user doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.94,0:21:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I recommend you will go and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.79,0:21:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,take advantage of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you were at the keynote,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or watched it online, one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that might have got you quite
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.68,0:21:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,excited was Apple Pay Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay Cash allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.04,0:21:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,send money to fellow users of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.23,0:21:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,iMessage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.12,0:21:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the money you received is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,kept inside Apple Pay Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.37,0:21:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Apple Pay Cash can be used
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.33,0:21:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in stores, physical stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can also be used within
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.77,0:21:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,apps and on the web, just like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,any other card.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.73,0:21:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if you can process
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.57,0:21:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,credit cards, you can process
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.21,0:21:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We will have more information on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.69,0:21:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what you need to do very
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.22,0:21:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly on our developer site.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.62,0:21:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But rest assured if you take
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,credit cards today, there will
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.09,0:21:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,be no real work to take Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.94,0:21:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.27,0:21:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few things you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.08,0:21:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,should know about Apple Pay Cash
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.25,0:22:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're in in-app or website
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.28,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay Cash is a stored
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,balance card.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.02,0:22:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me give you an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.41,0:22:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My business model for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.86,0:22:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,subscriptions wasn't really
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,working, so I've switched to an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.22,0:22:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on-demand model where we deliver
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.97,0:22:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the avocado toast directly to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.99,0:22:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.32,0:22:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, now I'm just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.61,0:22:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,one off charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.04,0:22:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm trying to make this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.26,0:22:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,payment with an Apple Pay Cash
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.56,0:22:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,card.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.15,0:22:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I don't have many
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.60,0:22:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,friends and they haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.48,0:22:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,actually sent me any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.68,0:22:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you'll see this UI is new.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.97,0:22:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It says insufficient balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.25,0:22:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing to note here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.74,0:22:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we're now using the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.18,0:22:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,total amount that you supply to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.33,0:22:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,determine whether the payment
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.63,0:22:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,can happen with Apple Pay Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.89,0:22:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that it's important
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.85,0:22:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that your total reflects what
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.37,0:22:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you intend to charge, Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.91,0:22:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Cash is only available when your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.44,0:22:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,balance exceeds the total being
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.22,0:22:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.96,0:22:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're not sure of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,total, you can use a pending
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.44,0:23:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.70,0:23:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Using a pending amount bypasses
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.32,0:23:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this behavior, we will allow the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,payment to happen regardless, of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.11,0:23:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,course bear in mind it may still
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.40,0:23:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,be like any stored value card,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.63,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rejected if the user doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,have a balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about some new API
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.95,0:23:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've added briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.16,0:23:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One use case we've been asked a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.26,0:23:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,lot about, particularly in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.22,0:23:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe is about limiting Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.18,0:23:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay to specific countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.16,0:23:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes this is required for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.81,0:23:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,regulatory compliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.73,0:23:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.12,0:23:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You just pass in this new
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.55,0:23:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,property, supportedCountries,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.03,0:23:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just set the countries
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to limit to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.07,0:23:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear in mind that like some of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,our other API that exists today,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.27,0:23:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that lets you say limit to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.75,0:23:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,credit or debit cards, this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.82,0:23:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't available on every single
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,card.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.60,0:23:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just bear that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.38,0:23:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.77,0:23:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,check out last year's session.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.89,0:23:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I want to talk about the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.61,0:23:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,biggest change that we're making
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.86,0:23:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to Apple Pay and that's to do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.69,0:23:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with error handling.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.40,0:24:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, things can go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.69,0:24:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with Apple Pay, I regret to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.70,0:24:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.24,0:24:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can be problematic to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.23,0:24:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate this to users today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.11,0:24:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had feedback from
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.81,0:24:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,developers, we've had feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.09,0:24:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from users.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.29,0:24:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some examples of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.37,0:24:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The payment instrument failed to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.02,0:24:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,process.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.48,0:24:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The billing address didn't match
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.33,0:24:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what the bank had on the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.39,0:24:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The email address was invalid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.79,0:24:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The postal address had an
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.17,0:24:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,incorrect zip or postal code.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.06,0:24:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The telephone was missing an
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.83,0:24:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,area code.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.13,0:24:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can divide these up into
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.70,0:24:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,two categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.32,0:24:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We can divide them up into what
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.64,0:24:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I call fatal errors and nonfatal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.54,0:24:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.21,0:24:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fatal errors are errors that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.67,0:24:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,can't actually be resolved by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.01,0:24:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the user there and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.22,0:24:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And you need to handle them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.25,0:24:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of Apple Pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.77,0:24:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're also often not
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.18,0:24:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,preventable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.32,0:24:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's an example of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.15,0:24:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The user has exceeded their
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.58,0:24:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,credit limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.36,0:24:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.94,0:25:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,solve that within Apple Pay,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.20,0:25:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to need to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.05,0:25:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your bank to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.05,0:25:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But many errors are nonfatal,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.93,0:25:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they can be resolved by the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.17,0:25:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.24,0:25:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can be handled within
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.82,0:25:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.19,0:25:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes they're
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.92,0:25:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,foreseeable and preventable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.88,0:25:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But in previous versions for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.91,0:25:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS, it was a little tricky to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.57,0:25:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate what exactly was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.92,0:25:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.34,0:25:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever a payment is complete
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.80,0:25:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the native API, you would
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.46,0:25:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,return a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.48,0:25:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentAuthorizationStatus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Enum.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.41,0:25:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have a similar Enum in the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.92,0:25:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,web API.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.46,0:25:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And these have no specificity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.47,0:25:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only say invalid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.70,0:25:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,shipping address, invalid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.98,0:25:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,billing, invalid contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.15,0:25:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the user's not really sure
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.75,0:25:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.75,0:25:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if the user could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.95,0:25:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,figure out what went wrong, they
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.40,0:25:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't actually able to edit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.76,0:25:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,existing values.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.21,0:25:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they'd have to go and pick
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.64,0:25:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,an entirely new address or type
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.02,0:25:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.42,0:25:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not a great
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.44,0:25:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.08,0:25:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we are changing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.39,0:25:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're changing it in three
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.65,0:25:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.88,0:25:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Firstly, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.01,0:25:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce some new guidelines to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.39,0:25:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,better handle user data.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.68,0:26:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also introduced a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.56,0:26:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,brand-new UI for users to input
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.71,0:26:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and edit data.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.54,0:26:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've tried out the iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.91,0:26:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Veetle, you might have seen
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.90,0:26:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.84,0:26:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, and perhaps most
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.32,0:26:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,excitingly for you, we've
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.50,0:26:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced new API to let you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.76,0:26:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate precise errors about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.84,0:26:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.73,0:26:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go through these one
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.79,0:26:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.68,0:26:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about handling user
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.18,0:26:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,data.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.71,0:26:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a fun one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.76,0:26:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Contact information on iOS and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.18,0:26:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,macOS can come from many
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.53,0:26:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,different sources.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.03,0:26:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It can come from iCloud, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.46,0:26:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,come from contacts manually
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.17,0:26:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,typed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.28,0:26:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can also come from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.28,0:26:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,LinkedIn, Facebook, VIDO,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.23,0:26:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible], it can come from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.56,0:26:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.41,0:26:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shouldn't expect this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.30,0:26:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,information to conform to your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.72,0:26:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,business logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.32,0:26:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.97,0:26:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is an example of a postal
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.07,0:26:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.93,0:26:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is for the Apple store in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.03,0:26:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Boston, which is a very nice
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.12,0:26:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple store.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.67,0:26:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You should visit, say hello,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.21,0:26:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tell them I sent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.47,0:26:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the address may look
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.89,0:27:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,correct to you, and if you wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.51,0:27:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this on an envelope and dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.89,0:27:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it in the mail, it would get
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.21,0:27:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.13,0:27:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's actually got a few
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.12,0:27:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,problems that could trick an
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.19,0:27:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,unwitting developer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.60,0:27:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them don't really seem
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.39,0:27:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like big problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.57,0:27:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Street is abbreviated.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.33,0:27:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like most systems should
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.35,0:27:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.34,0:27:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Some problems are a little more
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.77,0:27:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.92,0:27:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you paid attention in civics,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.93,0:27:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have noticed that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.92,0:27:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Massachusetts is misspelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.32,0:27:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It has two T's.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.35,0:27:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived there for four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.76,0:27:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't spell it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.87,0:27:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you were doing an exact
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.99,0:27:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,string match on the state, this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.86,0:27:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,might cause you a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.44,0:27:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing that's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.13,0:27:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,odd is this zip code.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.55,0:27:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It says zip plus 4, which is a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.67,0:27:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,regular zip code with 4
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.49,0:27:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,additional digits for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.52,0:27:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,specificity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.24,0:27:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If your backend system was only
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.19,0:27:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,expecting 5 digits, if your like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.40,0:27:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,database was only going to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.70,0:27:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,accept 5 numbers, you might hit
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.61,0:27:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,some problems ingesting this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.15,0:27:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Country is another example where
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.64,0:28:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you might trip up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.52,0:28:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a localized country
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.33,0:28:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.75,0:28:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's actually another field
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.39,0:28:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user doesn't see called
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.86,0:28:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,country code.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.81,0:28:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You should use that instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.97,0:28:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because country code is always
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.63,0:28:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.83,0:28:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in the language of the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.88,0:28:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.55,0:28:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you may well be like, OK I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.61,0:28:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,going to string match United
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.95,0:28:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,States, USA, all of its
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.37,0:28:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,variants.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.91,0:28:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, surprise, your user is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.50,0:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,French and this field is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,actually Etats-Unis and you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.34,0:28:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,can't now ingest it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.37,0:28:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, don't use country, use
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.26,0:28:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,country code.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.09,0:28:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone number also could trip
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.89,0:28:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It has some dashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.56,0:28:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your system was only set
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.89,0:28:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,up to accept numeric digits you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.83,0:28:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,could have some problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.92,0:28:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's also got a country
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.49,0:28:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,code, which could trip you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.03,0:28:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, be prepared for fuzzy input.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.31,0:28:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't force the user to comply
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.22,0:28:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with your business logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.66,0:28:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of techniques you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.81,0:28:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,can do to validate addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.85,0:28:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For example instead of using the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.06,0:28:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,state field directly you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.75,0:28:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,infer it from the zip code.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.70,0:28:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.77,0:29:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of tools to help
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.23,0:29:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you pass phone numbers, both
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.96,0:29:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,tolls available within iOS and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.79,0:29:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,also third party tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.87,0:29:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You might wonder, well why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.87,0:29:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't Apple Pay do this for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.22,0:29:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,me?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.77,0:29:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your business logic may
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.83,0:29:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,actually differ from another
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.32,0:29:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,merchant's business logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.52,0:29:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One merchant may only accept
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.39,0:29:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,phone numbers with a country
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.33,0:29:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.94,0:29:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Another merchant may only accept
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.75,0:29:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,phone numbers without.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.05,0:29:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't want the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.37,0:29:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,like have to create two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.36,0:29:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,different addresses, two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.71,0:29:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,different phone numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, don't force the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,comply with your business logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.39,0:29:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we are going to help you a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.86,0:29:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some new API's within
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.02,0:29:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the context framework to support
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.42,0:29:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,worldwide addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.79,0:29:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The example I gave for you was
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.27,0:29:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,from the US, but these problems
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.58,0:29:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,actually happen throughout the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.88,0:29:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.51,0:29:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There are new fields in contact
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.26,0:29:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for something that's called
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.61,0:29:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,supplementary sub-locality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.55,0:29:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very applicable in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.74,0:29:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In Japan, now, within Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.49,0:29:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you can request phonetic name in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.25,0:29:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,addition to regular name,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.90,0:29:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,another very important addition
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.65,0:29:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.67,0:29:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite all of these, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.95,0:29:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,despite your best intentions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.67,0:30:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,things can still go wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.05,0:30:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The USPS may be able to deliver
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.91,0:30:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this to Santa, but I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.56,0:30:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I know not where he lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.12,0:30:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are somethings that can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.92,0:30:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.57,0:30:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone number could just be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.92,0:30:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,missing digits entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.73,0:30:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The postal code and address
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.58,0:30:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.53,0:30:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The email address is misspelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.27,0:30:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The address is otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.97,0:30:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,unusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.40,0:30:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we're going to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.94,0:30:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,some new API to help you out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.72,0:30:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.45,0:30:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And we call it custom errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.92,0:30:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Custom errors let you gracefully
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.06,0:30:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,handle invalid or incorrect data
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.83,0:30:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in Apple Pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.87,0:30:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And they also let you display
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.43,0:30:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,custom error messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.89,0:30:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own error messages directly
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.74,0:30:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Apple Pay sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.35,0:30:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can direct the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.69,0:30:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,specific fields that need
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.21,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,correction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.67,0:30:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to my delightful
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.61,0:30:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,avocado toast app.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.07,0:30:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The delivery wasn't working, so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.77,0:30:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gone back to subscriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.60,0:30:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going for our series A
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.89,0:30:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,funding.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.79,0:30:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see here, I've got a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.24,0:30:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,shipping address error.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.37,0:31:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shipping address incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.00,0:31:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not very clear, but
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.24,0:31:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if the user taps in, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.84,0:31:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,actually see, now we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.14,0:31:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,custom error that was provided
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.94,0:31:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.49,0:31:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your zip code doesn't match your
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.70,0:31:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,city.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.21,0:31:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go through even
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.12,0:31:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,further, we'll actually
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.11,0:31:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,highlight the individual fields
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.23,0:31:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,for the user to correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.79,0:31:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see an example in Jon's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.77,0:31:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,demo, shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.60,0:31:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one unfortunate side effect
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.90,0:31:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of this is that we've had to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.85,0:31:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,deprecate a little bit of API.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.02,0:31:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All of our completion handlers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.92,0:31:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past in Apple Pay took,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.09,0:31:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as I mentioned this Enum.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.15,0:31:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we didn't really want to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.36,0:31:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,have hundreds of different Enums
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.81,0:31:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for each type of error.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.90,0:31:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead we're replacing them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.82,0:31:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.23,0:31:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, this is the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.25,0:31:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,delicate callback when a payment
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.73,0:31:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually authorized and you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.25,0:31:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,return a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.11,0:31:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentAuthorizationResult.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.24,0:31:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have to do little bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.89,0:31:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,renaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.14,0:31:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this result object contains
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.95,0:31:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a status and it contains an
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.61,0:31:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,array of errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.17,0:31:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the status is the status
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.61,0:32:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.47,0:32:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The payment was successful or
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.53,0:32:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,not.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.93,0:32:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you, for example, have a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.96,0:32:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,successful payment, you simply
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.29,0:32:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,return a result with no errors
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.47,0:32:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and a single status set.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.67,0:32:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But the errors themselves just
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.26,0:32:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,standard NS errors describing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.70,0:32:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.37,0:32:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Each error represents an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.59,0:32:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,individual problem with a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.85,0:32:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.67,0:32:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can chain errors
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.05,0:32:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,together.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.50,0:32:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can have more than one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.62,0:32:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user's email is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.19,0:32:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,phone is wrong, shipping is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.64,0:32:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.87,0:32:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just do it all in one
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.41,0:32:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you use NSError codes to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.41,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate the issue and User Info
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Keys on NSError to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.85,0:32:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,specific resolution steps and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.45,0:32:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.74,0:32:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, creating NSErrors can be a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.68,0:32:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit laborious and so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.90,0:32:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got some factory helpers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.60,0:32:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to assist you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.62,0:32:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example in Swift.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.58,0:32:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm creating a payment shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.28,0:32:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,address invalid error.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.64,0:32:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that this takes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.81,0:32:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,two properties at two
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.68,0:32:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,parameters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.65,0:32:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a CN contact key
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.51,0:32:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating the field that was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.03,0:32:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.37,0:32:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this case, the error is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.01,0:33:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the user put a wrong country in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.45,0:33:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we only deliver to the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.14,0:33:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I say CN postal address
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.62,0:33:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,country key.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.57,0:33:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the localized
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.97,0:33:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,description.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.75,0:33:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a localized error that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.03,0:33:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you provide that will be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.13,0:33:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed in the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.75,0:33:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in ES6 and JavaScript,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.80,0:33:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously NSError doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.79,0:33:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a new type called
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.62,0:33:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay Error.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.51,0:33:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can check for the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.48,0:33:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of this type to determine
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.94,0:33:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,whether Safari supports this new
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.03,0:33:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,API.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.03,0:33:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you provide the type of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.50,0:33:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,error, shipping contact is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.53,0:33:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,invalid.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.12,0:33:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The field it relates to,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.40,0:33:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,country, and your localized
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.05,0:33:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,description.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.82,0:33:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of our delegate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.92,0:33:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,callback have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.44,0:33:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's another example,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.83,0:33:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,didSelectShipingContract, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.46,0:33:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,takes an object,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.60,0:33:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentRequest
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.05,0:33:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ShippingContactUpdate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.74,0:33:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, like for like APIs are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.65,0:33:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,available in Safari 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.67,0:33:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari 11, only on iOS 11 and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.07,0:33:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,macOS High Sierra.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.37,0:33:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not support on Safari 11
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.16,0:33:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,running on older versions of the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.07,0:33:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,operating system.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.83,0:34:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, because JavaScript is a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.17,0:34:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,little more forgiving when it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.41,0:34:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,comes to API's we haven't had to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.65,0:34:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,actually make a deprecation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.09,0:34:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.67,0:34:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The existing completion
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.71,0:34:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,functions have nearly been
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.69,0:34:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,overloaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.78,0:34:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here is the old API, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.27,0:34:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,see we passed in individual
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.64,0:34:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,items, the total, the line
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.59,0:34:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,items, the status.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.94,0:34:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the new API, we simply pass
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.83,0:34:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.44,0:34:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're actually writing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.55,0:34:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay on web, this is a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.70,0:34:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty straightforward change
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.77,0:34:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.85,0:34:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you are writing Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.88,0:34:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay in application, I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.08,0:34:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,show you that it's really not
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.42,0:34:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that much work to implement this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.14,0:34:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,new API.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.59,0:34:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, I'm going to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.69,0:34:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jon to come up and he's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.28,0:34:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,give you a quick demo of how to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.37,0:34:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,migrate an Apple Pay App.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.21,0:34:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.52,0:34:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.26,0:34:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.03,0:34:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Jon and I'm going to show
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.37,0:34:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you how easy it is to update and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.45,0:34:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,existing Apple Pay project in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.38,0:34:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift, to the new API.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.65,0:34:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to be going
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.28,0:34:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,through four things today.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.96,0:34:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'll take a look at an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.65,0:34:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,existing project's code and see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.73,0:35:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,its current implementation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.35,0:35:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you've worked with Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.42,0:35:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay before, most of this stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.08,0:35:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will be familiar to you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.20,0:35:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, I'll deploy the app to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.76,0:35:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the simulator and interact with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.62,0:35:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apple Pay sheet as if I were
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.69,0:35:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a customer of your app trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.52,0:35:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,ship an item to one of my
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.22,0:35:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.50,0:35:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing I'll do is I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.52,0:35:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,update the code that we have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.26,0:35:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with the new API and show you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.13,0:35:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,three different errors that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.48,0:35:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we've introduced this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.45,0:35:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, I'll deploy the app
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.22,0:35:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,again to the simulator and show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.99,0:35:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you the differences in behaviors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.87,0:35:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,from the old Apple Pay sheet and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.58,0:35:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the new Apple Pay sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.27,0:35:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a look at what we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.46,0:35:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.43,0:35:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you can see, our app is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.92,0:35:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.73,0:35:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It has an image of the item that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.90,0:35:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to purchase, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.03,0:35:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a Buy with Apple Pay button.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.81,0:35:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's jump into the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.11,0:35:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The first function we have is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.55,0:35:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,viewDidLoad and in here, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.72,0:35:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,creating a PKPayment button,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.59,0:35:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,setting the type to buy and the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.33,0:35:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,style to black, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.36,0:35:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,adding it to the view.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.08,0:36:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the add to view function,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.03,0:36:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we're adding various constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.45,0:36:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to it as well as setting the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.07,0:36:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,target, when I click it to this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.31,0:36:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,next function, startPayment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.50,0:36:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.50,0:36:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here the first things we do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.45,0:36:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is create a few PKPayment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.23,0:36:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,summary items, as well as a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.30,0:36:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,PKShipping method.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.85,0:36:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the last thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.10,0:36:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,create an array of those objects
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.65,0:36:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that we'll later pass in to the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.65,0:36:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPayment request.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.66,0:36:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.52,0:36:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,payment request.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.75,0:36:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, it's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.06,0:36:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After we initialize it, we set
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.19,0:36:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the payment summary items to the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.18,0:36:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,items that we created before, as
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.10,0:36:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,well as set various properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.01,0:36:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,such as a merchant identifier,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.86,0:36:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.31,0:36:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Etcetera, etcetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.31,0:36:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing, this last line
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.17,0:36:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.73,0:36:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's required shipping contact
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.68,0:36:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.60,0:36:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a new property in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.20,0:36:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPayment request.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.99,0:36:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And here it takes in a set of PK
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.98,0:36:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,content fields and in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.26,0:37:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the developer is requesting the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.08,0:37:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,user provide an email address,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.16,0:37:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as a postal address.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.93,0:37:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the last thing we do in this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.55,0:37:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,function is create a PKPayment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.06,0:37:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization controller, with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.30,0:37:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this payment request that we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.39,0:37:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,created.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.35,0:37:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Set the delegate to ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.17,0:37:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and present it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.35,0:37:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.65,0:37:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.95,0:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.59,0:37:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The first function we have, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.36,0:37:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a didSelectShippingContact
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.77,0:37:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,function.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.75,0:37:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this gets called whenever
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.52,0:37:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apple Pay sheet first comes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.91,0:37:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,up, as well as whenever a user
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.42,0:37:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,edits one of their addresses, or
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.37,0:37:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,selects a new address.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.43,0:37:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can tell that this is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.41,0:37:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the old API because this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.73,0:37:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,completion block takes in a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.50,0:37:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentAuthorizationStatus
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.31,0:37:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Enum.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.44,0:37:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing to note is that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.01,0:37:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this contact information is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.65,0:37:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,actually redacted, so you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.19,0:37:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,get information like the email
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.82,0:37:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,address, the phone number, or
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.44,0:37:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the street until the user
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.01,0:37:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,authorizes the payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.14,0:37:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see what we have here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.97,0:37:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're doing some basic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.17,0:38:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,validation and in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.23,0:38:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we're just checking if the state
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.76,0:38:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is valid.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.75,0:38:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's not, we set the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.24,0:38:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,status to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.96,0:38:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,invalidShippingPostalAddress.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.16,0:38:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we set the payment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,status to success.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.35,0:38:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing we do, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.41,0:38:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,called the completion block,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.86,0:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with that paymentStatus, as well
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.88,0:38:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as the same shipping methods,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.58,0:38:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same payment summary
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.81,0:38:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,items.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.78,0:38:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you can update the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.17,0:38:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,shipping methods and the summary
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.63,0:38:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,items if you needed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.96,0:38:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But in this case, we're just
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.72,0:38:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,passing the same ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.91,0:38:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the next function we have is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.74,0:38:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the didAuthorizePaymentMethod.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.63,0:38:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And this gets called after the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.35,0:38:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,user authorizes the payment,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.30,0:38:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,using Touch ID, or with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.85,0:38:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Passcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.03,0:38:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And another thing to note is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.49,0:38:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that this PKPayment object
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.73,0:38:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,contains a property shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.53,0:38:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,contact, with the full contact
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.17,0:38:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.23,0:38:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're given the email
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.51,0:38:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,address, the phone and the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.02,0:38:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,street that you were not given
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.43,0:38:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.63,0:38:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we hope that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.84,0:38:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,validate the full contact
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.39,0:38:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,information in this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.30,0:38:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And for simplicity sake, all
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.88,0:39:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we're doing is checking the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.67,0:39:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,email, but you can do more of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.22,0:39:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.07,0:39:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the email check fails, we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.65,0:39:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,set the payment status to the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.88,0:39:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Enum invalidShippingContact.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.32,0:39:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it succeeds, we set the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.21,0:39:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,payment status to success.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.21,0:39:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing we do is call the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.24,0:39:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,completion block with that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.29,0:39:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,status.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.27,0:39:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see how this works
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.87,0:39:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,after we deploy it and interact
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.71,0:39:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Apple Pay sheet in the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.92,0:39:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.41,0:39:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the app comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.41,0:39:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We tap the buy with Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.57,0:39:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.03,0:39:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Apple Pay sheet comes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.08,0:39:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.85,0:39:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say I want to ship
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.97,0:39:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,this to my friend Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.09,0:39:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After I select shipping, I can
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.91,0:39:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,select add shipping address and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.47,0:39:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see, this is the new
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.95,0:39:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,UI to add a shipping address.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.56,0:39:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can either enter it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.83,0:39:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,manually or search one of your
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.60,0:39:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,contacts, or use one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.77,0:39:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,suggested locations that the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.10,0:39:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay sheet provides for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.73,0:39:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.40,0:39:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, I'm just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.06,0:39:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,select my friend Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.62,0:40:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She lives in Hawaii, so it might
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.08,0:40:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,be a little bit, there might be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.59,0:40:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,some problems with the address.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.11,0:40:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.32,0:40:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.22,0:40:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that the text is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.11,0:40:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,red so the user knows that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.87,0:40:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something wrong with the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.84,0:40:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.77,0:40:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not really clear where
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.33,0:40:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the issue is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.25,0:40:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As I look at it, the street
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.26,0:40:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,seems fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.50,0:40:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawaii is a valid state.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.74,0:40:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything looks fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.41,0:40:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, if I select that, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.39,0:40:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not a lot of information
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.51,0:40:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on what's wrong with the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.38,0:40:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.52,0:40:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my friend, Daniel, likes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.69,0:40:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this item as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.91,0:40:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he lives in California.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.27,0:40:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's just see if we can
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.51,0:40:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ship it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.32,0:40:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,After we got back, it looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.95,0:40:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no more error.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.13,0:40:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there must have been
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.81,0:40:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,something wrong with Sarah's
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.22,0:40:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,address, but it wasn't clear to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.78,0:40:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,me what was the actual issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.09,0:40:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's try to authorize this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.63,0:40:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,payment by hitting the Pay with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.23,0:40:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Passcode button.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.68,0:40:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Apple Pay sheet shows that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.95,0:40:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an error with the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.69,0:40:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.85,0:40:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, the text is highlighted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.42,0:40:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,red.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.22,0:41:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I select that, there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.78,0:41:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,clear text showing what's wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.13,0:41:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with this contact information.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.74,0:41:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be the percent sign, it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.74,0:41:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,could be just I don't like an
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.36,0:41:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,iCloud.com email address.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.41,0:41:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's just select Daniel's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.77,0:41:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,real email address to see how
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.99,0:41:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.54,0:41:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After we select that, we hit Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.46,0:41:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with Passcode and the payment
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.77,0:41:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,succeeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.82,0:41:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.17,0:41:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a user, it was really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.68,0:41:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to figure out what was
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.39,0:41:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong with the address that we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.53,0:41:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,had previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.85,0:41:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's implement the new APIs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.70,0:41:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.74,0:41:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the first function that we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.34,0:41:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have is a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.84,0:41:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,didSelectShippingContact method.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.55,0:41:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And here it takes in a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.94,0:41:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentRequest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.73,0:41:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,ShippingContactUpdate object.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.97,0:41:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing we want to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.82,0:41:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a local variable of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.72,0:41:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,update before and we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.30,0:41:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,initialize it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.91,0:41:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll initialize it afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.08,0:41:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,after we check the errors that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.84,0:41:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.88,0:42:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing we do is create
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.33,0:42:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,an array of errors that we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.39,0:42:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,append to as we validate the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.91,0:42:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.69,0:42:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, similar to before, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.61,0:42:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,checking if the state is valid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.64,0:42:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's not valid, instead
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.68,0:42:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of setting the status to an
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.50,0:42:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,invalid shipping address, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.42,0:42:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,append an error, a new type of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.01,0:42:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,error.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.60,0:42:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A paymentShipingAddress
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.97,0:42:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,UnserviceableError.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.51,0:42:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And in here, all it takes is a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.58,0:42:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,localized description.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.21,0:42:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this case, we're saying
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.83,0:42:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're unable to ship to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.27,0:42:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.60,0:42:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, we'll add another
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.94,0:42:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,check that we didn't do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.64,0:42:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,previously, which is check if
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.38,0:42:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the zip is valid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.04,0:42:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is another type of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.02,0:42:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,error a paymentShippingAddress
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.82,0:42:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,InvalidError.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.06,0:42:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And this takes in a key, a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.56,0:42:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,CNPostalAddress key.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.98,0:42:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this case we're taking a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.24,0:42:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,CNPostalAddress postal code key,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.57,0:42:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which tells PassKit to show
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.84,0:42:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,where the error is while the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.08,0:42:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,user tries to edit their
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.35,0:42:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,address.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.40,0:43:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, this takes in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.39,0:43:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,localizedDescription, the zip
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.91,0:43:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,code doesn't match the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.56,0:43:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so let's continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.04,0:43:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing we do is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.99,0:43:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,check if the errors array is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.45,0:43:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.10,0:43:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is, we'll initialize our
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.19,0:43:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,update object with the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.61,0:43:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,paymentSummaryItems, unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.83,0:43:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we'll initialize the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.26,0:43:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,update object with the errors as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.44,0:43:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,well as the payment summary
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.06,0:43:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,items and the shipping methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.58,0:43:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the last thing we do here is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.39,0:43:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,call the completion block, with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.79,0:43:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this new object.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.94,0:43:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's fix our
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.52,0:43:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,didAuthorizePayment function.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.41,0:43:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the old code that we
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.54,0:43:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have, so we can comment that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.86,0:43:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.73,0:43:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.15,0:43:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,similarly to before, is create
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.37,0:43:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,an array of errors that we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.86,0:43:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,append to.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.77,0:43:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we're checking one
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.17,0:43:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, which is if the email
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.01,0:43:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,address is valid or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.41,0:44:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's not, we'll append
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.76,0:44:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,another type of error, a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.24,0:44:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,paymentContactInvalidError.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.16,0:44:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of taking a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.01,0:44:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,CNPostalAddress key, this takes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.24,0:44:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in a PKContact field key.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.36,0:44:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And here, we're passing and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.97,0:44:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,email address so that it can
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.63,0:44:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,show in the correct location.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.68,0:44:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, and that takes another
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.02,0:44:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,localized description that will
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.95,0:44:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,be presented on the Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.14,0:44:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.48,0:44:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, we're checking if the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.21,0:44:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,errors array is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.38,0:44:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is, we'll set this status
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.10,0:44:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to success.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.05,0:44:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we'll set the status
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.93,0:44:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.97,0:44:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last thing we do is call
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.70,0:44:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the completion block with
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.82,0:44:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,initialize
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.45,0:44:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,PKPaymentAuthorizationResult,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.93,0:44:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,using that same status as well
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.63,0:44:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as the errors that we created.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.00,0:44:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see how this works
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.48,0:44:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,after we deploy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.32,0:44:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,After the app comes up, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.96,0:44:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,hit the Buy with Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.86,0:44:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,button once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.93,0:44:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And immediately we're presented
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.20,0:44:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.26,0:44:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The app doesn't ship to this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.38,0:45:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,shipping address.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.07,0:45:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is one of the new
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.40,0:45:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,errors that we've introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.36,0:45:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.60,0:45:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.62,0:45:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,unavailable text underneath out
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.51,0:45:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After I select that, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.46,0:45:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,text underneath our contact
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.52,0:45:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,saying unable to ship to this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.74,0:45:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,state.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.52,0:45:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is pretty clear to the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.95,0:45:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,user, saying that the app
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.96,0:45:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't support shipping to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.52,0:45:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.74,0:45:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try to ship this to my
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.50,0:45:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,friend, John Appleseed whose
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.23,0:45:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,shipping address is in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.30,0:45:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Cupertino.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.06,0:45:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After I select that, an error
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.37,0:45:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,shows up saying that the zip
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.50,0:45:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,code doesn't match the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.17,0:45:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I select that address,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.88,0:45:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the zip code is highlighted in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.79,0:45:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,red.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.64,0:45:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And because I know that 12345
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.54,0:45:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't the proper zip code to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.45,0:45:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Cupertino I can fix that and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.91,0:45:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,write 95014, hit done to save
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.39,0:45:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.98,0:45:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back, and I fixed all the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.25,0:45:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,contact information, or the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.53,0:45:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,address issues that I've had.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.34,0:46:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, let's try to pay with
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.75,0:46:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Passcode and see that we have an
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.82,0:46:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,error with our contact
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.35,0:46:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.68,0:46:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After we click that, we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.23,0:46:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an invalid character
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.50,0:46:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,found in the email, which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.33,0:46:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,percent sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.63,0:46:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as a user I can edit this
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,email address to remove that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.30,0:46:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,percent sign, or I can just
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.12,0:46:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,select another email address.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.20,0:46:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll select John Appleseed's
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.56,0:46:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,email address, at mac.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.06,0:46:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I went back, hit pay with
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.44,0:46:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Passcode, the payment should
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.30,0:46:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,authorize.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.47,0:46:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that shows you with the new
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.78,0:46:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs that we introduce in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.42,0:46:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,11, you have the power to give
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.87,0:46:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,more feedback to the user when
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.65,0:46:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with addresses on the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.14,0:46:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Pay sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.57,0:46:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we hope that this creates a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.15,0:46:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,better user experience, when
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.00,0:46:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,users are using Apple Pay within
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.72,0:46:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.44,0:46:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.52,0:46:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.05,0:46:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.90,0:46:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you all go off and take
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.62,0:46:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the time to update your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.72,0:47:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk briefly about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.95,0:47:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what's new with Wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.65,0:47:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've downloaded [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.20,0:47:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of iOS 11, you might have
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.75,0:47:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed one major thing that's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.24,0:47:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,new with Wallet, it looks a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.71,0:47:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.43,0:47:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.23,0:47:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also, if you haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.49,0:47:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,found it yet, a new mass
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.82,0:47:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,deletion management interface
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for your passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.98,0:47:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This new color scheme means that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.90,0:47:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probably a good time for
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.98,0:47:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you to revisit your past
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.39,0:47:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,designs.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.08,0:47:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at them, make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.48,0:47:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that they look great.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.41,0:47:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you never updated them to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.82,0:47:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,have watch assets or 3x assets,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.05,0:47:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,may be a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.61,0:47:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I also want to give you a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.34,0:47:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,quick update about NFC passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.26,0:47:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC passes are regular passes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.71,0:47:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that let you send customer
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.80,0:47:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,information over NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.56,0:47:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in iOS 11 we are only
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.70,0:47:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,going to support a more secure
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.51,0:47:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,type of NFC pass that we call
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.02,0:47:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,encrypted NFC passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.61,0:47:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to know more about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.51,0:47:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC passes, you can check out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.86,0:47:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,last year's session.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.98,0:47:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also go to our
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.42,0:47:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,developer's site and find out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.61,0:47:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,more, and register to take
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.52,0:48:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.66,0:48:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's one minor new
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.23,0:48:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,feature in Wallet this year for
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.72,0:48:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.17,0:48:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's sharing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.70,0:48:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Much requested feature, passes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.57,0:48:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can now be opted out sharing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.48,0:48:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is useful for single use
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.30,0:48:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,items like loyalty cards of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.27,0:48:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.06,0:48:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really easy to take
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.26,0:48:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.37,0:48:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a top level JSON key
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.38,0:48:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in your pass JSON.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.45,0:48:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is sharingProhibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.91,0:48:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your gift cards, your
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.58,0:48:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,loyalty cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.83,0:48:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You set this to true and the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.71,0:48:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,user can't share it via airdrop,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.86,0:48:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,iMessage.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.77,0:48:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a convenience feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.15,0:48:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,not a security feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.27,0:48:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, users can still share
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.73,0:48:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in other ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.51,0:48:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be supported on older
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.41,0:48:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,versions of iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.80,0:48:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's good if you need a good
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.43,0:48:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,reason to not allow the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.73,0:48:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,share for pure experience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.97,0:48:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.67,0:48:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's new with Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.66,0:48:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and Wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.01,0:48:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw some guidelines for
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.67,0:48:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,building best in brands Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.60,0:48:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay experiences, new API for
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.78,0:48:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,handling complex errors, and new
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.84,0:49:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,ways to share interact passes in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.17,0:49:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.31,0:49:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And for more information on any
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.85,0:49:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of these things, you can check
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.46,0:49:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,out our developer site.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.01,0:49:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something else you also
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.13,0:49:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,might want to check out and I
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.30,0:49:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,suspect a lot of you in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.64,0:49:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are extremely excited by.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.51,0:49:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the Core NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.94,0:49:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.18,0:49:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can read NFC tags on
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.85,0:49:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,supported hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.19,0:49:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have a special session
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.32,0:49:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's online only.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.64,0:49:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.64,0:49:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just search introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.70,0:49:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,CoreNFC on the WWDC site, check
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.69,0:49:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.62,0:49:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's everything from us for
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.83,0:49:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.58,0:49:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you go out now and have a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.04,0:49:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,great beer bash and I hope we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.63,0:49:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,see you next year to talk even
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.14,0:49:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,more about Apple Pay and Wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.84,0:49:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.52,0:49:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
